{"lemma":"مُطَّلِعُو","slug":"مُطَّلِعُو","root":"ط.ل.ع","root_slug":"ط-ل-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ل-ع","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُطَّلِع","root":"طلع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26957","n26958","n26959","n26960"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%84%D9%90%D8%B9%D9%8F%D9%88"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beginning, onset, outset"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the first line of a qasida or ghazal"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"rising of any celestial body","examples":[{"text":"Coordinate term: مَغْرِب (maḡrib)"},{"text":"سَلَامٌ هِيَ حَتَّىٰ مَطْلَعِ الْفَجْرِ","english":"It is all peace until the break of dawn."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"any place that celestial bodies rise.","examples":[{"text":"حَتَّىٰٓ إِذَا بَلَغَ مَطۡلِعَ ٱلشَّمۡسِ وَجَدَهَا تَطۡلُعُ عَلَىٰ قَوۡمٖ لَّمۡ نَجۡعَل لَّهُم مِّن دُونِهَا سِتۡرٗا","english":"until he reached the rising ˹point˺ of the sun. He found it rising on a people for whom We had provided no shelter from it."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ladder, stairs"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of طَلَعَ (ṭalaʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"well-informed, acquainted with, cognizant of"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Verbal noun and noun of place from the verb طَلَعَ (ṭalaʕa).\n\nDerived from the active participle of اِطَّلَعَ (iṭṭalaʕa, “to take insight”)."},"ipa":["/matˤ.laʕ/","/matˤ.liʕ/","/mutˤ.tˤa.liʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26957","headword_ar":"مَطْلَعٌ","root":"TlE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maToliEN","text_ar":"مَطْلِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are inf. ns.: and signify also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of rising"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the sun [&c.]: (S, O, K: [see 1, first sentence:]) but by Fr the former is explained as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rising,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter as meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of rising:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and some of the Basrees say that when one reads"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hat~aY maToliEi Alfajori","text_ar":"حَتَّى مَطْلِعِ الفَجْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the last verse of ch. xcvii. of the Kur], with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"l","text_ar":"ل"},{"kind":"text","text":", the meaning is, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the time of rising"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the dawn"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (O, TA:) [the pl.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTaAliEu","text_ar":"مَطَالِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"places"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"times"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of rising"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the sun [&c.]. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTolaEu Aljabali","text_ar":"مَطْلَعُ الجَبَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The place of ascent of the mountain."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA laka maTolaEa AlA^akamapi","text_ar":"هٰذَا لَكَ مَطْلَعَ الاَكَمَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This is present before thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as near to thee as if thou hadst to ascend for it the hill."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTolaEu AlqaSiydapi","text_ar":"مَطْلَعُ القَصِيدَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The beginning of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qSydp","text_ar":"قصيدة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ode"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muT~alaEN","text_ar":"مُطَّلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["O","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n26958","headword_ar":"مُطْلِعٌ","root":"TlE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  A palm-tree ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naxolapN","text_ar":"نَخْلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"putting forth its"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaloE","text_ar":"طَلْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]; and sometimes they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muToliEapN","text_ar":"مُطْلِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) ―         -b2-  And the latter, (assumed tropical:)  A palm-tree"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"taller than the other palm-trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"around it"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adjacent to it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n26959","headword_ar":"مُطَّلَعٌ","root":"TlE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place to which one ascends:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place of ascent from a low spot to a place that overlooks."},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA.) Hence, (TA,) it is said in a trad. (O, K) of the Prophet, (O,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAnazala mina","text_ar":"مَانَزَلَ مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlquroA=ni A=yapN A_il~aA lahaA ZahorN wabaTonN walikul~i HarofK Had~N walikul~i","text_ar":"القُرْا=نِ ا=يَةٌ اـِلَّا لَهَا ظَهْرٌ وَبَطْنٌ وَلِكُلِّ حَرْفٍ حَدٌّ وَلِكُلِّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Had~K muT~alaEN","text_ar":"حَدٍّ مُطَّلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (O, K) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Not a verse of the Kur-án has come down but it has an apparent and known"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exoteric"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interpretation and an intrinsic"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"esoteric"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"interpretation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ZahorN","text_ar":"ظَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", where see more,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and every word has a scope, and every scope has"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"point"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to which the knowledge thereof may ascend,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA,) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"something that may be violated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"God not having forbidden a thing that should be held sacred without his knowing that some one would seek to elicit it. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^otFY","text_ar":"مَاْتًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, K, TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muT~alaEu AlA^amori","text_ar":"مُطَّلَعُ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^otaAhu","text_ar":"مَاْتَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, TA;) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amori","text_ar":"الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTolaEu","text_ar":"مَطْلَعُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) i. e. (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of attaining to the doing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performing, of the affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maAlih`*aA AlA^amori muT~alaEN","text_ar":"مَالِهٰذَا الاَمْرِ مُطَّلَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of attaining to the doing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performing, of this affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ayona muT~alaEu h`*aA","text_ar":"اَيْنَ مُطَّلَعُ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^amori","text_ar":"الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA^otaAhu","text_ar":"مَاْتَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Where is the way of attaining to the doing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performing, of this affair?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, O, TA.) ―         -b3-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An elevated place from which one looks towards a low place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K, TA.) To this is likened the scene of the events of the world to come, (S, O, Msb, K, TA,) after death, i. e. the station of the day of resurrection, (TA,) in the saying of 'Omar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawo A^an~a maA fiY","text_ar":"لَوْ اَنَّ مَا فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aroDi jamiyEFA laA^afotadayotu bihi mino hawoli AlmuT~alaEi","text_ar":"الاَرْضِ جَمِيعًا لَاَفْتَدَيْتُ بِهِ مِنْ هَوْلِ المُطَّلَعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If all that is in the world belonged to me, assuredly I would ransom myself therewith from the terror of the place whence one will look down"},{"kind":"text","text":"on the day of resurrection]: (S, * O, Msb, * K, * TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuT~alaE","text_ar":"المُطَّلَع"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that which is looked upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"of such hardships as the interrogation of [the angels] Munkar and Nekeer, and the pressure of the grave, and its solitude, and the like; and is [for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuT~alaEi Ealayohi","text_ar":"المُطَّلَعِ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or] originally an inf. n. in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAiT~ilaAE","text_ar":"الاِطِّلَاع"},{"kind":"text","text":": or it may be a noun of time, and thus applied to the day of resurrection. (Har p. 344-5.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","O","K","S","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n26960","headword_ar":"مُطَّلِعٌ","root":"TlE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"powerful; high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who subdues,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overcomes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"powerful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDoTaliEN","text_ar":"مُضْطَلِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": or the latter has this meaning, from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~alaAEapu","text_ar":"الضَّلَاعَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the former signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"high,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eminent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who subdues,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overcomes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O:) accord. to ISk, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa muDoTaliEN","text_ar":"هُوَ مُضْطَلِعٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biHamolihi","text_ar":"بِحَمْلِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[“ he is one who has strength to bear it ”]; but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muT~aliEN bHmlh","text_ar":"مُطَّلِعٌ بحمله"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See, however,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muDoTaliEN","text_ar":"مُضْطَلِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DlE","text_ar":"ضلع"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["K","O"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}